frameDefinitions: A Dependent state-of-affairs has a Requirement as a prerequisite for obtaining or occurring.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
A Material has been processed (generally industrially) to some Degree in order to make it more useful for some (usually implicit) function.
An Exerter, Action, or Force is capable of exerting or does exert a physical force at a level specified by the target.
Unless a particular Required_situation obtains, Negative_consequences will follow.
frameExamples: The atomic bombings were probably not <t>necessary</t> to win WWII without a mainland invasion of Japan.
Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
Collect up the  <t>thawed</t> water from the freezer section.
Eugenie loved the sea and was a <t>strong</t> swimmer.
You <t>must</t> turn in your test by 5 p.m.
listRoleDefinitions: The state-of-affairs which cannot hold without the <fen>Requirement</fen>.
The entity or state-of-affairs that must be present or obtain in order for the <fen>Dependent</fen> to obtain.
An entity that has to be present for the <fen>Dependent</fen> state of affairs to obtain.
The time at which the <fen>Requirement</fen> is necessary for the <fen>Dependent</fen>.
<fen>Place</fen> denotes a location in which the specified relation between <fen>Requirement</fen> and <fen>Dependent</fen> holds.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.
The <fen>Alterant</fen> causes a change in the <fen>Material</fen>.
The <fen>Material</fen> is altered by the <fen>Agent</fen> in some useful way.
The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.
The substance which is altered in some useful way.
The <fen>Exerter</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Force</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Action</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
The location where the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
The state-of-affairs which prevents <fen>Negative_consequences</fen>.
The period during which the <fen>Required_situation</fen> is necessary to prevent negative consequences.
The location within which the <fen>Required_situation</fen> is required.
listRoleExamples: <fex>In the US</fex>, the political clout of big city mayors is necessary to put this on the national agenda.
Stu treated <fex>the lumber</fex> with magical waterproofing fairydust.
Salesmen touted the power <fex>of the engine's motor</fex>.
No one should underestimate the mighty <fex>strength</fex> of the dung beetle.
She gave him a playful, weak <fex>punch</fex> in the arm.
My quads feel particularly weak <fex>after 100 squats</fex>.
Muhammad Ali's force <fex>in the ring</fex> was indisputable.
He was told that <fex>when he got back</fex> , his column needed a serious rethink .
<fex>In California</fex> , seatbelts must be fastened at all times .
